strategy: Implement a two-phase aggregation that reduces the fact table early: first, join store_sales with the highly selective date_dim to get a reduced fact set with year, then aggregate by item_sk and year,
what_failed: Regression (0.94x): Restructured into a three‑CTE pipeline: first filter date_dim, then join with store_sales and aggregate by item_sk and year, finally join with filtered items. This reduces the fact table early, minimizes the hash‑join cost with item, and preserves exact output.
why_it_failed: Pre-filtered and joined store_sales to date CTE BEFORE the 3-way fact table join (store_sales <- store_returns <- catalog_sales). By materializing the date-filtered store_sales early, the optimizer loses the ability to push filters across the multi-way fact join and reorder joins optimally.
